info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 16 at 11:10AM AKDT until May 16 at 10:00PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING FOR AN ICE JAM IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM AKDT WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Flooding caused by an ice jam is occurring. * WHERE...Buckland River near Buckland. * WHEN...Until 1100 PM AKDT Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of the Buckland River due to an ice jam is imminent or occurring. Water will remain high until the ice jam releases. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1104 AM AKDT, Trained weather spotters reported an ice jam on the Buckland River near Buckland. Impounding water due to the ice jam will cause rapid river rises upstream. - - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood - If you live near or along the Buckland River, stay alert and be prepared to take action.
info.instruction: Rapid river rises are likely due to the history of the river flooding around Buckland. Take action immediately.
